REPLACE INTO multilingual(`key`,language,value,guid) values("abstract","en","The family Bonnetiaceae, comprising 35 species in three genera, is one of the nine malpighialean families which are unknown or poorly known with respect to chromosome numbers. Here we report the first exact chromosome count for the family based on Ploiarium alternifolium, using somatic cells from young leaves. The chromosome number of 2n = 22 indicates the base number of the genus to be x = 11. Comparisons with other Malpighiales suggest that x = 11 has occurred as a homoplasy several times within the order.","http://ci.nii.ac.jp/naid/110009596188");
